#: ../../../prop_fs/SKIP_UNITY_BUILD_INCLUSION.rst:2
msgid "SKIP_UNITY_BUILD_INCLUSION"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../prop_fs/SKIP_UNITY_BUILD_INCLUSION.rst:6
msgid ""
"Setting this property to true ensures the source files of the file set will "
"be skipped by unity builds when its associated target has its :prop_tgt:"
"`UNITY_BUILD` property set to true.  The source files of the file set will "
"instead be compiled on their own in the same way as it would with unity "
"builds disabled."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../prop_fs/SKIP_UNITY_BUILD_INCLUSION.rst:12
msgid ""
"This property helps with \"ODR (One definition rule)\" problems where "
"combining a particular source file with others might lead to build errors or "
"other unintended side effects."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../prop_fs/SKIP_UNITY_BUILD_INCLUSION.rst:16
msgid ""
"Note that :ref:`file sets <File Sets>`  of type ``HEADERS`` and "
"``CXX_MODULES`` as well as the sources which are scanned for C++ modules "
"(see :manual:`cmake-cxxmodules(7)`) are not eligible for unity build "
"inclusion and will automatically be excluded."
msgstr ""

